Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Ranacyclin E (XXA, UCSS1a; XXU; 1S=S, natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals, BBMm)

Literature Information.Literature: Chemical modification:  C-terminal amidation and one S-S bond.Activity: Active against Gram- Y. pseudotuberculosis YP III (MIC 9 uM), Ps. syringae pv tabaci (MIC 80 uM), Gram+ B. megaterium Bm11 (MIC 3 uM), S. lentus (MIC 7 uM), M. luteus (MIC 5 uM), fungi  C. tropicalis (MIC 7.4 uM), C. guiller-mondii (MIC 3.4 uM), P. nicotianae spores (MIC 32 uM).Toxicity: HC50 100 uM. Updated 2010; 5/2020.
Literature Information.Author: Mangoni ML, Papo N, Mignogna G, Andreu D, Shai Y, Barra D, Simmaco M2003
Literature Information.Title: Ranacyclins, a new family of short cyclic antimicrobial peptides: biological function, mode of action, and parameters involved in target specificity.
